Subject: Navier-Stokes Pressure Tail Decomposition Remainder Ledger

Description: Project-local math inquiry tool for splitting a bundled pressure-tail budget into pressure components before matching it to local epsilon-regularity quantities.

& [NavierStokesPressureTailDecompositionRemainderLedger] is a math inquiry tool
  + [tool_uuid] is 8e1e5e3a-c4b1-4d75-9a3f-bd17e61ce810
  + [project] is seven math problems
  + [problem] is Navier-Stokes Existence and Smoothness
  + [created_at] is 2026-06-27
  + [trigger_record] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\project_reflections\2026-06-27_navier_stokes_pressure_tail_conversion_scan_001.sop
  + [parent_audit] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\proof_inquiry\Navier_Stokes_Pressure_Bound_To_Epsilon_Audit.sop
  + [role] is prevent a pressure tail budget from being treated as pressure smallness before its local, harmonic, nonlocal, and cutoff components are separated
  + [not_role] is proving Navier-Stokes, validating pressure decomposition estimates, or asserting any component is small without a cited bound

& [LedgerColumnSet] is the decomposition surface
  + [component] is local_pressure_part, harmonic_pressure_part, nonlocal_far_field_part, cutoff_debris_part, pressure_work_part, or unclear
  + [source_status] is extracted, named_only, implicit, absent, or unclear
  + [accepted_pressure_quantity_match] is L3_over_2_pressure_smallness, pressure_oscillation_smallness, pressure_gradient_bound, pressure_work_only, none, or unclear
  + [same_frame_status] is same_cylinder, comparable_cylinder, larger_scale_only, global_only, conditional, or absent
  + [harmonic_or_nonlocal_risk] is low, medium, high, or unknown
  + [required_bound] is the exact estimate needed to feed a local epsilon criterion
  + [current_blocker] is the earliest missing feature blocking promotion
  + [admission_status] is admitted_for_pressure_audit, boundary_only, deep_research_needed, rejected_as_authority, or outside

& [UseProcedure] is the component audit workflow
  + [step_001_split] is list every pressure component hidden inside a tail budget or pressure-work term
  + [step_002_localize] is mark whether each component lives in the same cylinder as the regularity target
  + [step_003_match] is map each component to an accepted pressure quantity or mark it pressure_work_only or none
  + [step_004_risk] is mark harmonic or nonlocal risks before any smallness claim
  + [step_005_bound] is name the bound that would be required to admit the component to CKN-style pressure smallness
  + [step_006_status] is classify whether the component is admitted, boundary-only, or needs deep research

  = must: split harmonic pressure from nonlocal far-field pressure
  = must: separate pressure-work absorption from pressure-size or pressure-oscillation smallness
  = must: keep same-cylinder locality explicit
  = should: trigger Deep_Research_Priority_Gate when a component is named but its source lemma cannot be resolved from local artifacts
  - never: let a bundled tail budget count as L3_over_2 pressure smallness without component-level bounds

(navier_stokes_pressure_tail_decomposition_remainder_ledger) :tail budget, pressure split, target cylinder/ |component admission|
  + [inside] is pressure-tail decomposition before CKN or pressure-criterion matching
  + [boundary] is component separation creates audit clarity but not regularity proof
  |outside| proof promotion, source validation, and generic pressure-criterion summaries

