& [CurrentReading] is the developed proof-shape
  + [admission_result] is not_admitted_for_CKN_pressure_smallness
  + [reason] is local, harmonic, nonlocal, cutoff, and pressure-work components all require different bounds and cannot be bundled as one tail-budget smallness claim
  + [highest_value_next_component] is harmonic_pressure_part
  + [reason_for_priority] is harmonic pressure is both central to local pressure decomposition and the most dangerous place for false pressure-oscillation intuition
  + [deep_research_adjustment] is raw pressure oscillation language is insufficient unless the target theorem handles pressure modulo harmonic components or separately controls harmonic gradients and remainders
  + [Deep_Research_Priority_Gate] is ready_for_harmonic_pressure_component_if_next_reentry_needs_resolution
  + [proof_promotion_status] is blocked
